      <hedline>
        <hl1>Fuzzy Little Test Tubes</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Richard J Peppin letter on Lawrence Osborne's July 30 article opposes use of lab mice on moral grounds5</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Interesting article, and somewhat sympathetic to those lab animals that die in experiments of often dubious value. Osborne may have a heart, although his emphasis is on the researchers' needs. Independent of the questionable efficacy of the breeding and use of lab animals, the issue of morality stands out: how can we use sentient creatures for our purposes? Seems wrong.</p>
        <p>Richard J. Peppin  Silver Spring, Md.</p>
      </block>
